sentences: Siri Anne Nilsen (born 12 April 1985, Oslo, Norway) is a Norwegian singer-songwriter and voice actress.
Nilsen made her stage debut in 2007, and she was nominated for a Norwegian Grammy in the category of Best Female Artist in December, 2011.

Nilsen first performed publicly at Den Gode Kafe (The Good Cafe) in Oslo, April 2007.
In October 2008, Nilsen won a competition among new artists sponsored by the Norwegian record label, Grappa.
As part of the award, Nilsen received a record contract which produced 2009's Vi som ser i mørket (We Who See in the Dark).

Released on 5 October 2009, Nilsen's first record, Vi som ser i mørket (We Who See in the Dark), features songs written mostly in Norwegian, but also in English (Nilsen has mentioned that her American mother found it difficult to not want to proofread her English lyrics).
